body:
Throwing vs returning null caters to two different use cases:
* Throwing is better for users that always need the value since it provides more error information. This solution is also more inline with someday supporting validation at the option level instead of each caller implementing it as well.
* Returning null is better for uses who may optionally use a PipelineOption if its set since its easier for them to null check instead of try + catch + ignore.

I'm also in the throw category since returning null leads to information hiding.
LGTM!
I improved the test. However, as Cassandra only works with Java 8, I have to execute the tests only with Java 8 (not Java 7). I will do as we do in the java8 examples.
